**Competitor Content Approach & Weaknesses**
Top-ranking pages are either pure image galleries with thin editorial (Parade, WhoWhatWear) or generic "what are coffin nails" guides that mention length as one paragraph rather than anchoring the whole post to it. Almost no competitor writes specifically *for* the person who wants long coffin specifically — they write for "coffin" generally and add "long" as a modifier. Competitor tone is either listicle-flat or generic beauty-magazine cheerful. Nobody speaks to the aspirational psychology of choosing *long* — the statement it makes, the commitment it signals.

**Visual Patterns**
Top editorial competitors: 12–20 images (WhoWhatWear: 27 design images; Marie Claire: 16 images; Parade: 35 design images). The format is image-led with captions. This confirms long coffin is primarily a visual search — readers are screenshot-collecting, not deep-reading.

**Recommended Image Count:** 12–16 images. One strong anchor per H2 at minimum. Leads with most dramatic/aspirational images. Mix of single-nail close-ups and full-hand sets.

